[1] WHO Situation report 2 Dec 2015
Date: Wed 2 Dec 2015 [as of 29 Nov 2015]
Source: WHO [edited]
http://apps.who.int/ebola/current-situation/ebola-situation-report-2-december-2015


Summary
-------
No confirmed cases were reported in the week to 29 Nov 2015. Investigations are ongoing into the origin of infection of the cluster of 3 confirmed cases of Ebola virus disease (EVD) reported from Liberia in the week to 22 Nov 2015. The 1st-reported case in that cluster was a 15-year-old boy who tested positive for EVD after admission to a health facility in the Greater Monrovia area on 19 Nov 2015. He was then transferred to an Ebola treatment centre along with the 5 other members of his family; 2 other members of the family -- the boy's 8-year old brother and his 40-year-old father -- subsequently tested positive for EVD whilst in isolation. The 15-year-old boy died on 23 Nov 2015. In addition to the family of the 1st-reported case, 165 contacts have been identified so far, including 34 high-risk contacts. Liberia was previously declared free of Ebola transmission on 3 Sep 2015. ... - more

[Complete statistics in tables and charts may be seen at the source URL above]

